Subject: dxf: sanitize partially decoded values — zero handles, MTEXT columns

Two more corpus findings (1385 real-world DWGs), both "garbage in,
fatal DXF out":

* src/out_dxf.c (dxf_fixup_zero_handle): objects can arrive from
  partial decodes with handle 0 (LAYOUTs seen in the wild), which
  readers reject outright ("Invalid handle 0"), killing the whole
  file. Assign a fresh unique handle at write time; also give the
  synthetic ENDBLK of dxf_ENDBLK_empty a real handle instead of the 0
  that calloc leaves.
* src/dwg.spec (MTEXT): partial decodes leave garbage in column_type
  (256, 35141...); a 71 group > 2 in the embedded object crashes DXF
  readers (ezdxf ColumnType enum). Treat out-of-range values as "no
  columns".

All 254 unit tests pass. Sibling PRs from the same corpus hunt:
#1311 #1312 #1313 #1314.

Co-authored-by: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>


diff --git a/src/dwg.spec b/src/dwg.spec
index d97dac38..a7ac5201 100644
--- a/src/dwg.spec
+++ b/src/dwg.spec
@@ -2944,6 +2944,10 @@ DWG_ENTITY (MTEXT)
         FIELD_BD (extents_height, 43);
         // end redundant fields
 
+        // Partial decodes leave garbage here (256, 35141...); a 71 value
+        // > 2 crashes DXF readers (ezdxf ColumnType) — treat as "no columns"
+        if (FIELD_VALUE (column_type) > 2)
+          FIELD_VALUE (column_type) = 0;
         FIELD_BS (column_type, 71);
         if (FIELD_VALUE (column_type))
           {
diff --git a/src/out_dxf.c b/src/out_dxf.c
index 0e2e1726..5d761e42 100644
--- a/src/out_dxf.c
+++ b/src/out_dxf.c
@@ -1116,7 +1116,11 @@ static int dwg_dxf_TABLECONTENT (Bit_Chain *restrict dat,
     if (obj->handle.value)                                                    \
       LOG_TRACE ("handle: " FORMAT_H "\n", ARGS_H (obj->handle));             \
     if (dat->version > R_11 || dwg->header_vars.HANDLING)                     \
-      fprintf (dat->fh, "%3i\r\n" FMT_H "\r\n", 5, obj->handle.value);        \
+      {                                                                       \
